{
  "day": 63,
  "key": "day_63_death_and_burial",
  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-17",
  "title": {
    "en": "It Is Finished"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": ["After hours on the cross,", "Jesus spoke his final words."]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "death",
        "icon": "close",
        "label": { "en": "He Gave Up His Spirit" },
        "lines": [
          "Knowing that all was now completed,",
          "Jesus said,",
          "“I am thirsty.”",
          "After receiving the drink,",
          "he said,",
          "“It is finished.”",
          "Then he bowed his head",
          "and gave up his spirit."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "witness",
        "icon": "visibility",
        "label": { "en": "Witnessed and Confirmed" },
        "lines": [
          "The curtain of the temple",
          "was torn in two.",
          "The centurion said,",
          "“Surely he was the Son of God.”",
          "When the soldiers came to Jesus,",
          "they found that he was already dead.",
          "One pierced his side with a spear,",
          "bringing a flow of blood and water.",
          "The one who saw it",
          "has given testimony,",
          "and his testimony is true."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "burial",
        "icon": "inventory_2",
        "label": { "en": "Laid in a Tomb" },
        "lines": [
          "Joseph of Arimathea",
          "asked Pilate for the body.",
          "He wrapped it in linen cloth",
          "and placed it in a tomb",
          "cut out of rock.",
          "A stone was rolled",
          "against the entrance.",
          "The women saw",
          "where he was laid."
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "Jesus said, 'It is finished.' What do you think he meant? Why is it important that his death was witnessed and confirmed?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["John 19:28–35", "Mark 15:42–47"]
  }
}
